News and Publications

Belgium elected for a term on the UN Human Rights Council (2023-2025)

Minister of Foreign Affairs Hadja Lahbib welcomes the election of Belgium for a mandate at the United Nations Human Rights Council for the period 2023-2025.

Read More

20th European and World Day against the Death Penalty

October 10 marks the 20th European and World Day against the Death Penalty.

Read More

Belgium organises ministerial side event on fighting impunity on sexual violence - UNGA77 in New York

During her visit to New York for UNGA77 - the 77th General Assembly of the United Nations - Foreign Minister Hadja Lahbib will co-chair a side event with the European Commissioner for Crisis Management, Janez Lenarčič, and the Minister of Gender, Family and Children of the Democratic Republic of Congo, Gisèle Ndaya Luseba, on the fight against impunity for conflict-related sexual violence.

Read More

Belgium at the 77th session of the UN General Assembly in New York

The 77th session of the United Nations General Assembly will open in New York on September 19.
